Last Broadcast Date: Wed 6 Jun 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Matthew Bannister faces his fear of heights by taking a trip up the outside of a skyscraper called The Shard in London, which has just become Western Europe's tallest building. He meets some of the people from around the world who've built it. (Image: Crowds by the river cheer as the flotilla passes The Shard during the Thames Diamond Jubilee Pageant on the River Thames in London. Credit: AFP/Getty Images) Show less